1
00:01:54,599 --> 00:01:55,040
Miao Minzhi

2
00:01:55,700 --> 00:01:56,620
This Yang Xiaofang...

3
00:01:57,299 --> 00:01:59,000
going on blind dates with a huge belly every day.

4
00:01:59,299 --> 00:01:59,980
As the village director,

5
00:01:59,980 --> 00:02:01,040
shouldn't you do something about it?

6
00:02:01,980 --> 00:02:03,019
She's a grown young woman,

7
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:04,640
and she's not married.

8
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:06,540
Why should I interfere with her dating?

9
00:02:07,939 --> 00:02:08,819
The amusement park project,

10
00:02:09,060 --> 00:02:10,039
did you tell other people about it?

11
00:02:10,460 --> 00:02:12,240
Those men so eager to date her,

12
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:14,639
they must know about this.

13
00:02:15,379 --> 00:02:16,400
They're just after

14
00:02:16,539 --> 00:02:17,520
Xiaofang's compensation money.

15
00:02:17,819 --> 00:02:18,159
Right?

16
00:02:20,199 --> 00:02:21,479
Qi Deyao,

17
00:02:22,099 --> 00:02:23,659
even if she has a pretty face,

18
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:24,400
but...

19
00:02:24,780 --> 00:02:26,460
she's carrying Xiaowei's child!

20
00:02:26,780 --> 00:02:28,199
Otherwise, even if she were a fairy,

21
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:29,379
no one would want her.

22
00:02:30,439 --> 00:02:31,139
Qi Deyao,

23
00:02:32,419 --> 00:02:33,680
when you have a hammer,

24
00:02:33,919 --> 00:02:34,759
everyone looks like a nail.

25
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:36,180
What are they after?

26
00:02:36,599 --> 00:02:38,240
They're just after Xiaofang herself.

27
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:39,860
No matter what they're after,

28
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,080
you have to do something!

29
00:02:41,759 --> 00:02:42,520
Why should I?

30
00:02:43,319 --> 00:02:44,520
It's not like we're becoming in-laws.

31
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:45,919
Go talk to Fanhu yourself.

32
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:51,539
Me, go to Yang Fanhu?

33
00:02:52,580 --> 00:02:54,159
Bow my head to Yang Fanhu?

34
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:55,280
In his dreams!

35
00:02:57,099 --> 00:02:57,719
After her?

36
00:02:58,740 --> 00:03:00,060
Aren't they still after her compensation money?

37
00:03:00,919 --> 00:03:01,800
I absolutely won't let them

38
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:02,340
get what they want.

39
00:03:08,180 --> 00:03:08,699
Where are you rushing off to?

40
00:03:09,659 --> 00:03:10,860
Xiaowei's sitting idle at home.

41
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:12,879
None of your business whether he's idle!

42
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:14,560
Why so worked up? Can't I even mention it?

43
00:03:16,219 --> 00:03:16,939
Yang Fanhu,

44
00:03:17,479 --> 00:03:17,879
can you please

45
00:03:17,879 --> 00:03:19,139
rein in your daughter?

46
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:21,099
We've had our quarrels, sure,

47
00:03:21,740 --> 00:03:23,219
but look, I agreed to the bride price.

48
00:03:23,460 --> 00:03:24,599
Young couples fight,

49
00:03:24,599 --> 00:03:26,520
they sulk a couple days, then it's over.

50
00:03:27,180 --> 00:03:28,360
Xiaofang's gone too far!

51
00:03:28,599 --> 00:03:29,280
Going on blind dates everywhere,

52
00:03:29,860 --> 00:03:30,939
making this joke spread to the county.

53
00:03:30,939 --> 00:03:31,819
How am I supposed to show

54
00:03:31,879 --> 00:03:32,520
my face?

55
00:03:40,740 --> 00:03:41,520
You have a face left?

56
00:03:43,759 --> 00:03:45,400
Whether my daughter dates or not,

57
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:46,680
what's it got to do with you?

58
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:48,199
How is it none of my business?

59
00:03:48,780 --> 00:03:50,080
No matter what, Xiaofang

60
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:51,139
has to marry into our family.

61
00:03:52,979 --> 00:03:53,439
Says who?

62
00:03:54,319 --> 00:03:54,780
Why?

63
00:03:54,919 --> 00:03:55,860
"Says who?" "Why?"

64
00:03:56,159 --> 00:03:57,719
Because of the child in her belly!

65
00:03:58,060 --> 00:03:59,400
That's our Xiaowei's child.

66
00:04:03,740 --> 00:04:06,000
Which law says so?

67
00:04:06,099 --> 00:04:06,939
Show it to me!

68
00:04:08,259 --> 00:04:08,699
Yang Fanhu,

69
00:04:08,699 --> 00:04:10,060
you're talking law with me?

70
00:04:10,699 --> 00:04:11,520
Let me tell you,

71
00:04:11,900 --> 00:04:13,500
the law can't handle this.

72
00:04:13,860 --> 00:04:14,599
This is ethics,

73
00:04:14,979 --> 00:04:15,819
this is morality!

74
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:17,339
Use some common sense,

75
00:04:17,660 --> 00:04:18,220
okay?

76
00:04:19,639 --> 00:04:20,579
Sure, sure.

77
00:04:20,819 --> 00:04:21,480
What are you doing?

78
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:23,779
If you won't talk law with me,

79
00:04:24,759 --> 00:04:26,019
I'll talk fists with you!

80
00:04:27,379 --> 00:04:28,100
Yang Fanhu,

81
00:04:28,639 --> 00:04:29,379
your daughter's reckless,

82
00:04:29,399 --> 00:04:30,800
and you're just as reckless as she is!

83
00:04:43,180 --> 00:04:43,740
Your own wife

84
00:04:43,740 --> 00:04:45,139
is out there chasing after other men,

85
00:04:45,379 --> 00:04:45,980
and you still have the nerve

86
00:04:45,980 --> 00:04:46,899
to sit here reading?

87
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:49,720
Didn't you say nobody wants Xiaofang?

88
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:50,500
So what's the rush?

89
00:04:50,620 --> 00:04:50,899
You...

90
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:53,699
You're so calm sitting here.

91
00:04:53,699 --> 00:04:55,240
Have you come up with some plan?

92
00:04:55,519 --> 00:04:57,079
Xiaofang likes herbs.

93
00:04:57,160 --> 00:04:59,660
She said she'd gather herbs for the baby.

94
00:05:01,060 --> 00:05:01,819
I get it now.

95
00:05:02,740 --> 00:05:03,819
You're doing this to win her over,

96
00:05:03,860 --> 00:05:04,860
catering to her interests, right?

97
00:05:05,180 --> 00:05:06,779
But how long are you gonna read?

98
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:09,720
Fine, I'll stop reading.

99
00:05:10,379 --> 00:05:11,100
Okay? I'll stop.

100
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:11,920
Okay, read, read, read.

101
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:12,759
Okay, read on. I won't bother you.

102
00:05:12,959 --> 00:05:13,240
Okay.

103
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:14,779
Hurry up and finish.

104
00:05:17,060 --> 00:05:18,120
So noisy, chattering away.

105
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:21,959
Mushrooms.

106
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:34,759
Xiaofang!

107
00:05:35,319 --> 00:05:37,000
How can you walk backwards over here?

108
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:38,240
That's impressive!

109
00:05:38,779 --> 00:05:39,680
What are you doing?

110
00:05:40,399 --> 00:05:41,639
Making your tears flow back in?

111
00:05:47,019 --> 00:05:47,720
It doesn't hurt, doesn't hurt.

112
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:49,220
Xiaofang.

113
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:50,139
I...

114
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:52,160
You went on that blind date,

115
00:05:53,699 --> 00:05:54,420
and I was so upset

116
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:56,279
I couldn't eat properly,

117
00:05:56,779 --> 00:05:57,699
couldn't sleep properly.

118
00:06:06,660 --> 00:06:07,939
Did you eat these poisonous mushrooms?

119
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:08,620
Xiaofang!

120
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:15,819
Lean against the tree.

121
00:06:36,319 --> 00:06:37,180
What is this?

122
00:06:37,740 --> 00:06:38,279
Poison.

123
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:44,439
Xiaofang, you did the right thing.

124
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:46,199
I really do deserve to die.

125
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:49,839
You once laid your sincere love

126
00:06:49,939 --> 00:06:51,439
right there in front of me.

127
00:06:51,740 --> 00:06:52,139
Qi Xiaowei.

128
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:53,579
You brought this pain on yourself.

129
00:06:53,740 --> 00:06:55,160
This won't make me get back with you.

130
00:06:58,579 --> 00:06:59,180
Get back together?

131
00:07:00,660 --> 00:07:02,139
Xiaofang wants to get back with me!

132
00:07:03,660 --> 00:07:04,259
Xiaofang!

133
00:07:05,339 --> 00:07:06,740
You're getting back with me!

134
00:07:27,899 --> 00:07:29,000
This Master Jia

135
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:30,279
is quite a well-known figure

136
00:07:30,319 --> 00:07:31,879
throughout the surrounding villages.

137
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,519
He specializes in resolving inner turmoil

138
00:07:34,779 --> 00:07:36,300
and clearing the mind.

139
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:40,920
Master Jia, I've heard so much about you.

140
00:07:46,339 --> 00:07:47,699
Uncle Yang, have some tea.

141
00:07:49,199 --> 00:07:49,980
By all accounts,

142
00:07:51,300 --> 00:07:52,639
my body normally

143
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:54,779
doesn't have any real issues.

144
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:58,279
So why do I feel so weak,

145
00:07:58,740 --> 00:07:59,480
so uneasy inside?

146
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,779
What have I got to be uneasy about?

147
00:08:05,079 --> 00:08:06,180
I've already retired.

148
00:08:06,540 --> 00:08:08,300
You have no grandchildren.

149
00:08:08,819 --> 00:08:10,100
That's the source of your unease.

150
00:08:10,779 --> 00:08:11,639
You've got something weighing on your heart.

151
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:25,060
Master, you're absolutely right.

152
00:08:27,420 --> 00:08:28,920
What I lack is a grandson.

153
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:31,600
But may I ask, Master,

154
00:08:33,580 --> 00:08:35,279
how can I stop feeling this way?

155
00:08:48,299 --> 00:08:49,340
In your family,

156
00:08:50,460 --> 00:08:52,919
do you have any close relatives

157
00:08:53,519 --> 00:08:54,419
who are already pregnant

158
00:08:55,100 --> 00:08:56,340
and about to give birth?

159
00:08:57,759 --> 00:08:58,600
I don't think so.

160
00:09:00,379 --> 00:09:00,879
No.

161
00:09:03,139 --> 00:09:03,779
Actually, there is one.

162
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:08,679
Take a look.

163
00:09:09,639 --> 00:09:11,220
"Single mom bravely seeking marriage."

164
00:09:11,220 --> 00:09:12,000
What in the world is this?

165
00:09:12,379 --> 00:09:13,320
Going on blind dates with a kid?

166
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:14,779
Isn't that a disgrace?

167
00:09:14,919 --> 00:09:15,559
Old boss,

168
00:09:16,659 --> 00:09:17,700
this is Yang Xiaofang.

169
00:09:19,679 --> 00:09:20,600
Who? Xiaofang?

170
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:22,879
Yang Shu's granddaughter.

171
00:09:23,179 --> 00:09:23,559
Right.

172
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:26,080
She's a proper close relative of yours,

173
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,940
and Xiaofang is pregnant.

174
00:09:30,740 --> 00:09:31,460
That's it, then.

175
00:09:32,139 --> 00:09:33,320
The child in her belly

176
00:09:33,700 --> 00:09:35,460
is your source of strength.

177
00:09:35,539 --> 00:09:36,659
Once you have him,

178
00:09:36,860 --> 00:09:38,139
your heart won't feel empty anymore.

179
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:41,360
Xiao Shu,

180
00:09:41,919 --> 00:09:42,799
hurry up.

181
00:09:43,159 --> 00:09:44,679
Go to the Yang family and find Xiaofang.

182
00:09:45,419 --> 00:09:45,779
Yes.

183
00:09:47,740 --> 00:09:48,299
Mr. Yang,

184
00:09:48,679 --> 00:09:50,179
your credit card is long overdue.

185
00:09:50,399 --> 00:09:51,299
We're hoping you can

186
00:09:51,340 --> 00:09:52,299
pay it off as soon as possible.

187
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,659
I mean, look at you,

188
00:09:53,820 --> 00:09:55,860
calling yesterday, today, every single day.

189
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:57,379
Aren't you sick of it?

190
00:09:57,659 --> 00:09:58,659
Not at all, Mr. Yang.

191
00:09:58,820 --> 00:09:59,740
This is my job.

192
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,100
I have to remind you

193
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,139
that the consequences of

194
00:10:02,139 --> 00:10:03,200
an unpaid, overdue credit card

195
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:04,159
are very serious.

196
00:10:04,379 --> 00:10:04,940
I don't have the money.

197
00:10:04,940 --> 00:10:05,500
That's all I've got to say.

198
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:06,379
"No money, no money."

199
00:10:06,580 --> 00:10:07,059
Look,

200
00:10:07,259 --> 00:10:08,120
if there's really no other way,

201
00:10:08,159 --> 00:10:09,480
just ask your family for help.

202
00:10:09,559 --> 00:10:10,299
Fine, fine, fine, I got it.

203
00:10:10,620 --> 00:10:11,039
Stop calling.

204
00:10:11,259 --> 00:10:12,679
Don't be so stubborn about it.

205
00:10:15,539 --> 00:10:16,700
Who am I supposed to ask? Who?

206
00:10:38,179 --> 00:10:38,519
Hello.

207
00:10:38,899 --> 00:10:39,379
Who are you looking for?

208
00:10:40,519 --> 00:10:41,779
I'm here for the Yang family.

209
00:10:42,279 --> 00:10:42,779
The Yang family?

210
00:10:42,919 --> 00:10:43,259
Yes.

211
00:10:43,740 --> 00:10:44,960
Which department are you a leader of?

212
00:10:46,659 --> 00:10:47,600
Not quite yet.

213
00:10:48,899 --> 00:10:49,860
Thanks for the kind words.

214
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:51,460
He'll be a big shot in the future.

215
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:52,659
Oh, no, no.

216
00:10:56,340 --> 00:10:56,779
Zhu'er.

217
00:10:57,539 --> 00:10:58,759
Yang Fanzhu.

218
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:01,980
Shu Qingcang.

219
00:11:02,539 --> 00:11:02,860
You...

220
00:11:03,940 --> 00:11:04,779
What are you doing here?

221
00:11:05,659 --> 00:11:06,440
Looking for you.

222
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:07,899
For me?

223
00:11:09,460 --> 00:11:09,820
You...

224
00:11:11,139 --> 00:11:12,500
I hardly recognized you.

225
00:11:13,299 --> 00:11:14,360
How long has it been?

226
00:11:14,419 --> 00:11:15,879
Over ten years, I think.

227
00:11:15,879 --> 00:11:16,440
About ten years.

228
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:17,620
I remember when you...

229
00:11:17,620 --> 00:11:18,639
first left to make your way.

230
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:19,919
I only came up to your chest.

231
00:11:20,019 --> 00:11:21,080
Yeah, time flies.

232
00:11:21,740 --> 00:11:22,700
Now you come up to mine.

233
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:24,340
Look at you.

234
00:11:24,700 --> 00:11:26,019
In that suit,

235
00:11:26,559 --> 00:11:27,960
you look sharp!

236
00:11:28,340 --> 00:11:30,100
It's just work attire.

237
00:11:31,279 --> 00:11:31,960
That car...

238
00:11:32,779 --> 00:11:33,460
Is that yours?

239
00:11:34,740 --> 00:11:35,539
Just for getting around.

240
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,360
Man, you're doing well.

241
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:38,240
You... you...

242
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:40,519
Where are you working now?

243
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:44,580
Nothing fancy, really.

244
00:11:48,399 --> 00:11:49,240
What's that noise?

245
00:11:58,019 --> 00:11:58,480
Uncle.

246
00:11:59,120 --> 00:11:59,580
How is he?

247
00:12:00,340 --> 00:12:01,740
Nothing serious.

248
00:12:02,559 --> 00:12:04,299
The antidote Xiaofang gave him,

249
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:05,480
it's fine, works well.

250
00:12:06,659 --> 00:12:08,679
It's been days, and he's still like this.

251
00:12:08,820 --> 00:12:09,700
And you call that fine?

252
00:12:10,039 --> 00:12:10,919
Come on, Uncle,

253
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,500
do you actually know what you're doing?

254
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:14,419
Anyone who eats poison mushrooms

255
00:12:14,659 --> 00:12:16,019
gets loopy for a few days.

256
00:12:16,580 --> 00:12:18,340
If he likes singing, just let him sing.

257
00:12:18,340 --> 00:12:19,080
Let him sing.

258
00:12:20,220 --> 00:12:21,559
Our family's pig,

259
00:12:21,559 --> 00:12:22,539
after eating poison mushrooms,

260
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:24,820
for a whole month, thought it was human.

261
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:26,820
Stood up and talked back to me every day.

262
00:12:27,860 --> 00:12:29,659
Give him this medicine, this one.

263
00:12:30,679 --> 00:12:31,460
This is for dogs.

264
00:12:31,539 --> 00:12:32,399
Here, this is for humans.

265
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:33,360
This one, okay.

266
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:38,559
Okay, okay.

267
00:12:39,019 --> 00:12:39,360
Uncle.

268
00:12:39,460 --> 00:12:40,139
Thanks for your trouble.

269
00:12:40,740 --> 00:12:41,759
I won't see you downstairs.

270
00:12:41,879 --> 00:12:42,360
No need, no need.

271
00:12:42,860 --> 00:12:43,639
Quick, hold him down!

272
00:12:43,919 --> 00:12:44,220
Hurry!

273
00:12:48,220 --> 00:12:48,919
Look at you,

274
00:12:48,919 --> 00:12:50,519
saving money at your son's expense.

275
00:12:50,940 --> 00:12:51,639
Getting a vet?

276
00:12:51,639 --> 00:12:52,419
What does he know?

277
00:12:52,679 --> 00:12:54,000
You think your son's a pig?

278
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:54,779
You got that right.

279
00:12:55,220 --> 00:12:56,379
Running off to eat poison mushrooms.

280
00:12:56,379 --> 00:12:57,340
If he's not a pig, what is he?

281
00:12:57,519 --> 00:12:58,419
Fine, sing, sing, sing.

282
00:12:58,519 --> 00:12:58,860
Come on.

283
00:12:59,220 --> 00:12:59,899
Yell louder.

284
00:12:59,980 --> 00:13:00,279
Come on.

285
00:13:00,700 --> 00:13:01,379
Yell over this way.

286
00:13:01,519 --> 00:13:02,659
Shut it, let them hear!

287
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:04,320
Sing!

288
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:05,580
Sing that way.

289
00:13:05,820 --> 00:13:06,659
Let the neighbors hear.

290
00:13:06,899 --> 00:13:07,279
Sing!

291
00:13:13,379 --> 00:13:14,559
You pighead!

292
00:13:14,919 --> 00:13:16,100
You little brat, who are you calling a pig?

293
00:13:16,220 --> 00:13:18,039
You beast, ordering me around?

294
00:13:19,460 --> 00:13:20,059
What are you doing?

295
00:13:20,659 --> 00:13:20,940
No!

296
00:13:21,679 --> 00:13:22,080
Xiaowei!

297
00:13:22,399 --> 00:13:23,100
You little brat!

298
00:13:23,259 --> 00:13:24,139
You've gone mad, mad!

299
00:13:24,139 --> 00:13:25,399
Xiaowei, Xiaowei, Xiaowei!

300
00:13:25,399 --> 00:13:26,240
Don't hurt yourself, Xiaowei!

301
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:26,960
He's gone mad, mad!

302
00:13:27,279 --> 00:13:27,679
Mad!

303
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:28,559
Mad, mad!

304
00:13:28,860 --> 00:13:29,299
Mad!

305
00:13:40,179 --> 00:13:42,259
Your boss is my uncle?

306
00:13:42,919 --> 00:13:43,200
Yes.

307
00:13:43,639 --> 00:13:44,299
I've been driving

308
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:45,340
for Uncle Yang for years now.

309
00:13:46,019 --> 00:13:46,779
Didn't he

310
00:13:47,259 --> 00:13:48,899
retire years ago?

311
00:13:49,159 --> 00:13:49,519
He did.

312
00:13:49,799 --> 00:13:50,820
But the company's busy,

313
00:13:51,059 --> 00:13:52,320
and Uncle Yang keeps saying

314
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:53,440
he's not up to it anymore.

315
00:13:54,379 --> 00:13:55,860
Then why are you still driving for him?

316
00:13:56,559 --> 00:13:57,019
Well,

317
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:59,120
I'm interning at the company now,

318
00:13:59,179 --> 00:14:01,399
so Uncle Yang still has to lead the way on a lot of things.

319
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:04,720
My uncle arranged this for you?

320
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:06,340
Yes.

321
00:14:06,580 --> 00:14:08,460
That's why Uncle Yang's my benefactor.

322
00:14:08,980 --> 00:14:10,039
He may have retired,

323
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:12,299
but we can't just give him the cold shoulder, right?

324
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:13,000
Exactly.

325
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:18,519
So I want to serve him well,

326
00:14:18,759 --> 00:14:19,519
enrich

327
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:20,500
and make the most of

328
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:22,740
his retirement years.

329
00:14:24,860 --> 00:14:25,679
That's the right attitude.

330
00:14:25,879 --> 00:14:26,559
As a person,

331
00:14:26,960 --> 00:14:28,379
you should repay kindness.

332
00:14:29,179 --> 00:14:30,460
These are plums from our farm.

333
00:14:30,940 --> 00:14:31,539
Try some.

334
00:14:31,639 --> 00:14:32,120
Have plenty.

335
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:32,960
They're really delicious.

336
00:14:33,759 --> 00:14:34,259
Thank you.

337
00:14:34,419 --> 00:14:36,419
We haven't been in touch for over a decade.

338
00:14:36,539 --> 00:14:37,679
Coming by out of the blue,

339
00:14:37,940 --> 00:14:39,419
is there something going on?

340
00:14:41,779 --> 00:14:43,019
What could there be?

341
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:45,120
Uncle Yang's getting on in years,

342
00:14:45,279 --> 00:14:45,860
feeling nostalgic.

343
00:14:46,159 --> 00:14:48,600
Mid-Autumn Festival's coming up,

344
00:14:48,980 --> 00:14:50,379
so let the family reunite

345
00:14:50,620 --> 00:14:51,299
and have a lively time.

346
00:14:51,860 --> 00:14:52,340
Xiaofang,

347
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:53,899
do you remember Grand-uncle?

348
00:14:54,220 --> 00:14:54,940
Vaguely.

349
00:14:55,820 --> 00:14:56,919
Grand-uncle was pretty fierce.

350
00:14:57,139 --> 00:14:57,440
Grandma,

351
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:58,419
do you remember that year

352
00:14:58,879 --> 00:14:59,840
when he tried to hit me for something?

353
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:00,860
You even argued with him.

354
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:02,679
Mom, one New Year,

355
00:15:02,940 --> 00:15:04,419
what was it Xiaofang did

356
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:05,580
that got Uncle so angry?

357
00:15:05,980 --> 00:15:06,940
Xiaofang

358
00:15:07,059 --> 00:15:09,419
broke your uncle's teapot,

359
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:10,980
and he wanted to hit her.

360
00:15:11,159 --> 00:15:11,559
Right.

361
00:15:11,700 --> 00:15:12,700
Grand-uncle raised his hand to slap me,

362
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:13,559
right in the face.

363
00:15:13,559 --> 00:15:14,740
My dad rushed up and grabbed him like this.

364
00:15:15,299 --> 00:15:15,779
What's wrong?

365
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:16,960
Did you pull something? What is it?

366
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:18,019
What is it? You didn't pull anything, did you?

367
00:15:18,279 --> 00:15:18,820
To the hospital!

368
00:15:18,860 --> 00:15:19,639
Hospital, hospital!

369
00:15:19,779 --> 00:15:20,580
Quick, start the car!

370
00:15:20,980 --> 00:15:21,379
Let's go!

371
00:15:21,659 --> 00:15:22,220
Take mine,

372
00:15:22,559 --> 00:15:23,799
my four-wheel-drive sedan.

373
00:15:28,019 --> 00:15:28,419
I...

374
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:33,220
Don't panic, it's okay.

375
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:34,879
Auntie,

376
00:15:35,679 --> 00:15:37,299
why do I feel like since I came back,

377
00:15:37,679 --> 00:15:39,100
my belly's grown a lot bigger?

378
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:40,120
Of course.

379
00:15:40,860 --> 00:15:42,460
The family's been feeding you well.

380
00:15:42,940 --> 00:15:44,620
The baby's growing by leaps and bounds.

381
00:15:44,759 --> 00:15:46,059
But the days ahead

382
00:15:46,559 --> 00:15:47,600
are going to be tough.

383
00:15:48,299 --> 00:15:49,659
The fetus is developing healthily.

384
00:15:49,980 --> 00:15:50,799
First child, right?

385
00:15:51,799 --> 00:15:52,139
Yes.

386
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:53,840
Here, look.

387
00:15:54,879 --> 00:15:56,259
This is the baby's head.

388
00:15:57,019 --> 00:15:58,100
This is the baby's leg.

389
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:00,059
So fun.

390
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:10,679
So amazing!

391
00:16:21,539 --> 00:16:21,980
Doctor

392
00:16:22,639 --> 00:16:23,539
Is this...

393
00:16:24,159 --> 00:16:25,799
Does it look like a boy?

394
00:16:26,799 --> 00:16:27,820
If you think so, then it is.

395
00:16:28,159 --> 00:16:29,340
If you don't, then it isn't.

396
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:31,059
I don't mean anything by it.

397
00:16:31,279 --> 00:16:32,220
I just wanted to ask.

398
00:16:32,419 --> 00:16:33,620
Should we prepare some...

399
00:16:33,620 --> 00:16:34,539
little dresses,

400
00:16:34,580 --> 00:16:35,899
or little pants, you know?

401
00:16:36,460 --> 00:16:37,940
Auntie, stop asking.

402
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:39,659
Boy or girl, we'll love it.

403
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:41,740
Get both dresses and pants ready.

404
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:43,759
That's a lot to prepare!

405
00:16:44,059 --> 00:16:45,460
Doctor, can't you give us a hint?

406
00:16:46,019 --> 00:16:47,019
All right, the exam is done.

407
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:49,799
Right, right, right.

408
00:16:49,899 --> 00:16:51,019
Your hospital has rules.

409
00:16:51,279 --> 00:16:51,600
Come on.

410
00:16:52,379 --> 00:16:53,080
Let me wipe it off for you.

411
00:16:54,740 --> 00:16:56,100
Get up slowly.

412
00:16:58,500 --> 00:16:58,840
Come on.

413
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:00,159
Put your shoes on.

414
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:01,840
Here.

415
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:06,500
As long as everything's fine.

416
00:17:08,140 --> 00:17:08,579
Yan'er.

417
00:17:08,819 --> 00:17:09,400
Brother, brother, Dad.

418
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:09,900
Don't worry.

419
00:17:10,099 --> 00:17:10,640
The doctor said

420
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:12,680
mother and baby are both healthy.

421
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:14,000
Take a look.

422
00:17:14,599 --> 00:17:15,039
Look,

423
00:17:16,119 --> 00:17:16,779
isn't he...

424
00:17:16,799 --> 00:17:17,960
crossing his legs?

425
00:17:18,259 --> 00:17:19,359
Lying flat at such a young age.

426
00:17:19,380 --> 00:17:20,339
That's way too comfy!

427
00:17:21,059 --> 00:17:22,960
Will he even want to come out?

428
00:17:23,579 --> 00:17:24,539
No, no, no.

429
00:17:25,420 --> 00:17:27,339
He wants to come out and meet me too.

430
00:17:28,900 --> 00:17:30,079
Here, this is...

431
00:17:30,799 --> 00:17:31,579
It's a boy!

432
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:33,400
A boy, great, a boy!

433
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:34,099
Xiao Shu,

434
00:17:34,140 --> 00:17:35,200
why are you so excited?

435
00:17:35,359 --> 00:17:36,299
You like kids too?

436
00:17:36,900 --> 00:17:38,559
I do. A boy's great, a boy's great!

437
00:17:39,039 --> 00:17:39,880
A girl's great too.

438
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:41,660
Right, both are great.

439
00:17:42,339 --> 00:17:42,960
A boy's great.

440
00:17:51,779 --> 00:17:52,539
Look at that cloud.

441
00:17:52,539 --> 00:17:53,799
It looks like Cupid.

442
00:17:54,380 --> 00:17:55,779
I saw it in Xiaowei's studio.

443
00:17:57,380 --> 00:17:58,099
Who is this?

444
00:17:59,559 --> 00:18:00,160
Cupid.

445
00:18:00,759 --> 00:18:01,779
He symbolizes love.

446
00:18:02,339 --> 00:18:03,279
He's a little angel.

447
00:18:05,339 --> 00:18:06,220
A little angel.

448
00:18:12,119 --> 00:18:12,819
I've decided.

449
00:18:14,019 --> 00:18:15,440
I'll name him Cupid.

450
00:18:15,880 --> 00:18:16,319
Call him what?

451
00:18:17,099 --> 00:18:17,779
Yang Bite.

452
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,680
That's quite a foreign-sounding name.

453
00:18:21,140 --> 00:18:22,220
Great name.

454
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:23,720
Cupid, I know him.

455
00:18:23,940 --> 00:18:24,599
He's that...

456
00:18:24,839 --> 00:18:25,900
little boy who shoots arrows,

457
00:18:25,900 --> 00:18:26,259
right?

458
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:27,519
Yes, the one who loves shooting arrows.

459
00:18:27,519 --> 00:18:28,220
Right, right, right.

460
00:18:28,380 --> 00:18:29,019
A boy, a boy.

461
00:18:29,140 --> 00:18:29,880
A boy's great, a boy's great.

462
00:18:30,579 --> 00:18:31,400
A girl's great too.

463
00:18:38,960 --> 00:18:39,460
Jingjing.

464
00:18:41,220 --> 00:18:41,680
Jingjing.

465
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:43,579
Jingjing!

466
00:18:44,859 --> 00:18:46,039
I've been calling you forever.

467
00:18:46,220 --> 00:18:47,079
Didn't you hear me?

468
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:49,640
You... you're here too?

469
00:18:50,779 --> 00:18:52,160
Didn't you say you were in Guangzhou

470
00:18:52,180 --> 00:18:53,299
and not coming home for the holiday?

471
00:18:53,599 --> 00:18:54,720
I felt like coming, so I came.

472
00:18:55,460 --> 00:18:56,119
Well, if you're coming back,

473
00:18:56,240 --> 00:18:57,859
you should've told me in advance, right?

474
00:18:57,859 --> 00:18:58,319
Right?

475
00:18:58,819 --> 00:19:00,140
What are you doing at the hospital?

476
00:19:01,460 --> 00:19:02,940
What else would I be here for?

477
00:19:03,599 --> 00:19:04,160
I'm sick.

478
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:06,140
You're sick?

479
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:07,420
What kind of illness?

480
00:19:09,859 --> 00:19:10,319
A serious one.

481
00:19:12,539 --> 00:19:13,460
Give me some money for treatment.

482
00:19:14,759 --> 00:19:15,279
Jingjing.

483
00:19:15,599 --> 00:19:16,460
Don't be scared.

484
00:19:16,740 --> 00:19:18,180
No matter what illness, don't worry.

485
00:19:18,380 --> 00:19:19,559
I bought medical insurance.

486
00:19:19,819 --> 00:19:20,599
Whatever illness you have,

487
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:22,079
they have to pay for it.

488
00:19:22,140 --> 00:19:22,859
Okay, okay, okay.

489
00:19:22,980 --> 00:19:23,359
I'm not sick.

490
00:19:24,740 --> 00:19:26,039
Not sick? You just said you were!

491
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:26,940
Are you sick or not?

492
00:19:27,539 --> 00:19:28,180
Not sick.

493
00:19:31,619 --> 00:19:31,960
You...

494
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:34,160
Then why are you at the hospital?

495
00:19:37,339 --> 00:19:39,839
Don't tell me you got a boyfriend

496
00:19:40,519 --> 00:19:41,539
and got in trouble?

497
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,500
What are you thinking?

498
00:19:43,519 --> 00:19:44,500
It's Grandma who's sick.

499
00:19:46,619 --> 00:19:47,819
But you said you were sick.

500
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:50,920
How about this? Come here.

501
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:52,920
I'll...

502
00:19:54,079 --> 00:19:54,640
give you

503
00:19:55,339 --> 00:19:56,400
some money.

504
00:19:56,759 --> 00:19:58,819
Buy Grandma some supplements.

505
00:19:59,819 --> 00:20:00,359
A hundred thousand.

506
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:01,599
How much?

507
00:20:02,680 --> 00:20:03,359
A hundred thousand.

508
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:06,920
All to save Grandma's life.

509
00:20:08,059 --> 00:20:09,019
Where are you?

510
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:10,640
Mom!

511
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:11,440
Mom!

512
00:20:12,579 --> 00:20:13,319
Son!

513
00:20:13,319 --> 00:20:13,779
Mom!

514
00:20:14,660 --> 00:20:15,980
I missed you so much!

515
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:21,299
Where's your dad?

516
00:20:21,579 --> 00:20:22,279
Dad didn't come.

517
00:20:22,759 --> 00:20:23,640
He had me come by myself.

518
00:20:24,019 --> 00:20:25,480
You came by yourself?

519
00:20:26,259 --> 00:20:27,799
He made you travel all that way alone?

520
00:20:28,220 --> 00:20:29,839
Debt collectors come knocking every day.

521
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:32,099
Boss Qian said he has to lay low.

522
00:20:32,460 --> 00:20:33,140
He couldn't take me with him.

523
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:35,140
So basically he stayed in Shenzhen

524
00:20:35,279 --> 00:20:35,880
and I came to find you.

525
00:20:36,359 --> 00:20:37,619
So you're not going to school?

526
00:20:38,039 --> 00:20:39,519
Dad got me a month's sick leave.

527
00:20:40,359 --> 00:20:40,759
Mom.

528
00:20:41,160 --> 00:20:41,680
What is it?

529
00:20:42,039 --> 00:20:42,960
You didn't want me to come?

530
00:20:45,680 --> 00:20:46,400
About your dad's situation,

531
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:47,960
I don't want the family to know.

532
00:20:48,579 --> 00:20:49,619
Keep your mouth shut.

533
00:20:51,019 --> 00:20:51,579
Whoever asks me,

534
00:20:51,579 --> 00:20:52,920
I'll just say Dad's busy with work.

535
00:20:53,420 --> 00:20:54,220
Busy counting money.

536
00:20:59,240 --> 00:21:00,619
Remember what I told you.

537
00:21:02,740 --> 00:21:04,539
Uncle Hu's quiet, remember to greet him.

538
00:21:04,980 --> 00:21:07,099
Your other uncle talks a lot, just tune him out.

539
00:21:07,140 --> 00:21:08,460
Watch out for Auntie Fanyan.

540
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:09,579
She's obsessed with saving face.

541
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:10,960
Loves to compete with me.

542
00:21:11,420 --> 00:21:12,200
Don't let her find out

543
00:21:12,220 --> 00:21:13,059
that our family's struggling.

544
00:21:13,180 --> 00:21:13,880
Or she'll laugh at us.

545
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:15,740
Who told you that?

546
00:21:22,599 --> 00:21:24,000
Qian Dandan

547
00:21:24,019 --> 00:21:26,119
You've gotten chubbier again!

548
00:21:26,859 --> 00:21:27,279
Sis

549
00:21:28,319 --> 00:21:29,740
Pregnant women all gain weight.

550
00:21:29,740 --> 00:21:30,539
How come you didn't?

551
00:21:32,380 --> 00:21:33,180
Back in my day,

552
00:21:33,279 --> 00:21:34,680
when I was pregnant with your sister Jingjing,

553
00:21:34,740 --> 00:21:35,500
I stayed slim too.

554
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:36,960
Well, when I was pregnant with you,

555
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:37,960
I didn't gain weight either.

556
00:21:38,119 --> 00:21:39,140
Let me do it. Go eat.

557
00:21:40,339 --> 00:21:41,299
Pour some broth on it.

558
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:43,599
Because you're all such well-behaved kids.

559
00:21:44,779 --> 00:21:45,119
What's up?

560
00:21:45,119 --> 00:21:45,640
Get up for a sec.

561
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:49,619
Sis,

562
00:21:50,460 --> 00:21:51,240
is it gonna be a nephew?

563
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:54,180
It might be a niece, you know.

564
00:21:54,279 --> 00:21:55,279
Whatever you have is fine.

565
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:56,680
I'm happy for you either way.

566
00:21:56,980 --> 00:21:58,039
Boys and girls are equal anyway.

567
00:21:58,059 --> 00:21:58,900
Same thing.

568
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,319
The hell are you happy about?

569
00:22:01,220 --> 00:22:01,700
Eat.

570
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:03,960
Come on, Mom, sit down and eat.

571
00:22:04,119 --> 00:22:05,380
Fanyan, put it here.

572
00:22:05,539 --> 00:22:06,200
Right in front of him.

573
00:22:08,299 --> 00:22:08,779
Dandan,

574
00:22:09,180 --> 00:22:09,940
have some meat.

575
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:11,960
Grandma's the best!

576
00:22:13,119 --> 00:22:13,480
Here.

577
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:15,279
Grandma missed you, Dandan.

578
00:22:15,700 --> 00:22:16,920
This meat's made just for you.

579
00:22:16,920 --> 00:22:17,500
Come on, take a bite.

580
00:22:17,500 --> 00:22:18,099
It's all yours.

581
00:22:18,359 --> 00:22:19,200
Thanks, Grandma!

582
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:21,059
Is it good?

583
00:22:21,559 --> 00:22:22,200
So delicious!

584
00:22:22,619 --> 00:22:24,420
I haven't had such tasty braised pork in ages.

585
00:22:24,420 --> 00:22:24,940
Grandma!

586
00:22:24,940 --> 00:22:25,880
Eat up, eat up.

587
00:22:26,140 --> 00:22:27,539
That's 'cause your mom's a cheapskate.

588
00:22:28,019 --> 00:22:29,980
Starving Dandan, no meat for him.

589
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:31,440
All she knows is spending money.

590
00:22:31,859 --> 00:22:34,019
Buying herself new clothes, jewelry.

591
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:37,180
Your mom's so rich, all she's got is money.

592
00:22:38,019 --> 00:22:38,759
What else can I do but pinch pennies?

593
00:22:39,299 --> 00:22:40,200
What if Dandan grows up

594
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:41,339
and turns out like his sister Jingjing?

595
00:22:42,019 --> 00:22:43,539
Just two phone calls a year.

596
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:45,180
When I'm old, no one to care for me.

597
00:22:45,900 --> 00:22:46,839
Then don't I have to

598
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:47,859
save up for retirement myself?

599
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:49,980
What's wrong with providing for yourself?

600
00:22:50,539 --> 00:22:52,339
That's called not burdening your kids.

601
00:22:53,140 --> 00:22:55,079
You think raising kids means they'll take care of you?

602
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:56,940
The end result is always

603
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:59,480
getting shipped off to a nursing home by your daughter-in-law.

604
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:01,440
Dandan,

605
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:02,839
how could your dad bear

606
00:23:02,859 --> 00:23:04,440
to let you come back all alone?

607
00:23:04,599 --> 00:23:05,519
What's he so busy with?

608
00:23:11,859 --> 00:23:13,380
His dad's busy collecting project payments.

609
00:23:16,220 --> 00:23:17,839
Quit fishing for gossip.

610
00:23:18,660 --> 00:23:19,500
Have some sense of boundaries,

611
00:23:19,539 --> 00:23:20,539
you hear me, Yang Fanyan?

612
00:23:22,299 --> 00:23:23,799
I'm just chatting with the kid.

613
00:23:23,799 --> 00:23:25,140
What nerve did I hit with you?

614
00:23:25,759 --> 00:23:26,619
Boundaries, my foot.

615
00:23:26,859 --> 00:23:27,480
Do you even have any?

616
00:23:29,140 --> 00:23:29,779
Every time you come back,

617
00:23:29,799 --> 00:23:31,259
you're all high and mighty,

618
00:23:31,660 --> 00:23:32,900
strutting in those sky-high heels,

619
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:33,799
like you wanna trample everyone

620
00:23:33,799 --> 00:23:34,799
under your feet.

621
00:23:35,079 --> 00:23:35,799
What happened this time?

622
00:23:35,799 --> 00:23:37,160
Only brought one pair of heels?

623
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:38,960
Don't tell me

624
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:41,019
your old man Qian went bankrupt?

625
00:23:41,799 --> 00:23:42,440
Mom, you...

626
00:23:42,839 --> 00:23:43,900
I didn't say it.

627
00:23:44,980 --> 00:23:46,500
Auntie guessed it herself.

628
00:23:50,839 --> 00:23:52,119
Qian Dan,

629
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:54,599
let's go.

630
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:56,619
Mom!

631
00:23:57,180 --> 00:23:57,680
Mom!

632
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:58,900
I really didn't say it.

633
00:23:58,900 --> 00:24:00,279
Old Qian really did go bankrupt?

634
00:24:01,019 --> 00:24:02,539
It can't be true, can it?

635
00:24:06,940 --> 00:24:08,980
Auntie clearly guessed it herself.

636
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:10,779
Why are you hitting me?

637
00:24:11,619 --> 00:24:12,680
Stop hitting me!

638
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:13,519
Don't bother trying to stop her.

639
00:24:36,319 --> 00:24:36,900
What's wrong?

640
00:24:37,180 --> 00:24:38,319
Got too much energy to burn?

641
00:24:42,059 --> 00:24:42,380
Here.

642
00:24:42,819 --> 00:24:43,700
Eat these noodles.

643
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:46,640
Laughing at my expense, are you happy now?

644
00:24:50,019 --> 00:24:51,299
I knew something was up with you.

645
00:24:51,900 --> 00:24:53,019
Every time you came back before,

646
00:24:53,180 --> 00:24:54,819
you'd swagger around showing off,

647
00:24:55,119 --> 00:24:56,240
running here and there,

648
00:24:56,940 --> 00:24:58,759
afraid nobody knew you married a rich guy.

649
00:24:59,480 --> 00:25:00,279
But this time,

650
00:25:00,700 --> 00:25:02,299
you won't set a foot outside.

651
00:25:03,140 --> 00:25:04,079
No matter what,

652
00:25:04,079 --> 00:25:05,859
you shouldn't hide things from family.

653
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:07,619
Still putting on a brave face.

654
00:25:07,859 --> 00:25:08,640
Aren't you exhausted?

655
00:25:09,519 --> 00:25:10,079
Yang Fanyan.

656
00:25:10,079 --> 00:25:10,819
Don't stand there

657
00:25:10,819 --> 00:25:12,339
shedding crocodile tears.

658
00:25:12,799 --> 00:25:13,339
Ever since we were kids,

659
00:25:13,339 --> 00:25:15,099
you've always been fake and phony.

660
00:25:15,519 --> 00:25:16,319
Mom says you're sensible,

661
00:25:16,319 --> 00:25:17,640
outsiders say you're respectable,

662
00:25:17,960 --> 00:25:19,480
only I know how phony you really are.

663
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:23,680
That damn Old Qian,

664
00:25:24,900 --> 00:25:26,579
he's dragged me and my kid down like this,

665
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:28,099
forced to hide out in the village,

666
00:25:28,099 --> 00:25:29,339
becoming a laughingstock.

667
00:25:30,779 --> 00:25:31,740
That bastard!

668
00:25:32,440 --> 00:25:33,519
Once I'm back, I'm divorcing him!

669
00:25:40,900 --> 00:25:42,200
You've never held a job in your life.

670
00:25:43,599 --> 00:25:44,779
Divorced with a kid to raise.

671
00:25:46,180 --> 00:25:47,220
How are you gonna make money?

672
00:25:48,180 --> 00:25:49,079
How are you gonna support the kid?

673
00:25:50,299 --> 00:25:50,839
Besides,

674
00:25:51,559 --> 00:25:52,839
a woman your age,

675
00:25:53,339 --> 00:25:54,680
what kind of man could you even marry?

676
00:25:55,279 --> 00:25:56,640
No matter what,

677
00:25:57,819 --> 00:25:59,720
Old Qian is Dandan's real father.

678
00:25:59,799 --> 00:26:00,200
Right?

679
00:26:00,579 --> 00:26:01,779
And he's got a sharp mind.

680
00:26:02,079 --> 00:26:03,440
He'll find a way to make money.

681
00:26:03,440 --> 00:26:04,119
He still has connections.

682
00:26:04,319 --> 00:26:05,119
Just bear with it.

683
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:06,700
Get through this rough patch with him.

684
00:26:06,900 --> 00:26:07,420
Can't you do that?

685
00:26:09,579 --> 00:26:10,559
How am I supposed to get through it?

686
00:26:11,500 --> 00:26:13,599
The debt he owes isn't small.

687
00:26:14,119 --> 00:26:15,200
If it weren't for Dandan,

688
00:26:15,720 --> 00:26:16,799
I'd have divorced him long ago.

689
00:26:17,940 --> 00:26:18,460
If you divorce,

690
00:26:18,859 --> 00:26:19,720
who gets Dandan?

691
00:26:20,960 --> 00:26:22,500
I'm not as clear-headed as you.

692
00:26:23,819 --> 00:26:24,960
Even if we had to live on scraps,

693
00:26:25,900 --> 00:26:27,359
I'd never abandon Dandan.

694
00:26:28,680 --> 00:26:29,839
I'm capable of raising him well.

695
00:26:33,480 --> 00:26:33,819
Right.

696
00:26:35,359 --> 00:26:36,119
Don't be like me.

697
00:26:37,720 --> 00:26:38,740
Ended up so pathetic that

698
00:26:39,319 --> 00:26:40,660
even my own daughter

699
00:26:41,059 --> 00:26:41,920
refuses to acknowledge me.

700
00:26:42,759 --> 00:26:43,460
A hundred thousand.

701
00:26:44,200 --> 00:26:45,759
It's all for Grandma's life-saving treatment.

702
00:26:46,099 --> 00:26:46,859
Consider it a loan from me.

703
00:26:47,279 --> 00:26:48,480
I'll definitely pay you back later.

704
00:26:49,859 --> 00:26:50,160
But...

705
00:26:50,940 --> 00:26:52,680
I don't have that much in my account.

706
00:26:53,119 --> 00:26:53,960
And right around the holidays too.

707
00:26:53,960 --> 00:26:55,059
Where am I supposed to scrape it together?

708
00:26:55,059 --> 00:26:55,839
Fine, I get it.

709
00:26:56,220 --> 00:26:57,680
If you don't wanna give it, just say so.

710
00:26:58,220 --> 00:26:59,619
What kind of attitude is that?

711
00:27:01,339 --> 00:27:02,380
Am I still your mother or not?

712
00:27:02,720 --> 00:27:04,079
What gives you the right to talk to me like that?

713
00:27:05,519 --> 00:27:06,559
Every time I see you,

714
00:27:06,740 --> 00:27:07,539
you've got a sour face.

715
00:27:07,740 --> 00:27:09,559
Silent as a stone, not a single word.

716
00:27:09,740 --> 00:27:10,900
And when you finally do speak up,

717
00:27:11,180 --> 00:27:12,440
first thing out of your mouth is a hundred thousand.

718
00:27:14,039 --> 00:27:15,119
Let's be fair here.

719
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:17,079
Your grandma getting sick

720
00:27:17,539 --> 00:27:18,660
has nothing to do with me.

721
00:27:19,500 --> 00:27:21,119
Your dad and I divorced long ago.

722
00:27:23,299 --> 00:27:24,279
Whoever's supposed to pay,

723
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:25,900
it shouldn't fall on me, right?

724
00:27:26,940 --> 00:27:27,839
Why shouldn't it?

725
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:30,680
Have you cared for me all these years?

726
00:27:31,079 --> 00:27:32,200
It was Grandma who worked her fingers to the bone

727
00:27:32,220 --> 00:27:33,039
to raise me.

728
00:27:33,519 --> 00:27:34,980
Now she's sick and needs money.

729
00:27:35,180 --> 00:27:36,799
I think you're the one who should pay.

730
00:27:37,660 --> 00:27:39,119
I've never cared for you?

731
00:27:40,140 --> 00:27:40,819
Every month,

732
00:27:40,900 --> 00:27:42,059
right on time,

733
00:27:42,279 --> 00:27:43,180
I sent your living expenses

734
00:27:43,279 --> 00:27:44,579
straight to your dad's card.

735
00:27:45,099 --> 00:27:46,680
I work my butt off out there every day.

736
00:27:46,839 --> 00:27:47,839
Who am I doing it for?

737
00:27:48,240 --> 00:27:49,539
Isn't it all for you?

738
00:27:50,119 --> 00:27:51,500
I never cared for you?

739
00:27:52,380 --> 00:27:54,160
Have a conscience when you speak.

740
00:27:57,440 --> 00:27:57,819
Fine.

741
00:27:59,279 --> 00:28:00,140
I have no conscience.

742
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:01,059
Right.

743
00:28:02,640 --> 00:28:03,019
You do.

744
00:28:04,420 --> 00:28:05,059
You have a conscience.

745
00:28:06,819 --> 00:28:08,460
Help me pay Grandma's medical bills.

746
00:28:08,859 --> 00:28:09,299
Okay?

747
00:28:10,119 --> 00:28:10,960
I'm begging you.

748
00:28:43,519 --> 00:28:44,900
Did Jingjing upset you again?

749
00:28:47,660 --> 00:28:48,339
Don't mention her.

750
00:28:49,980 --> 00:28:51,380
It's all my own doing.

751
00:28:52,680 --> 00:28:53,920
How old is this girl now?

752
00:28:53,920 --> 00:28:55,440
Why is she still so immature?

753
00:28:56,200 --> 00:28:57,000
I'm gonna call and ask her

754
00:28:57,019 --> 00:28:57,700
what she really wants.

755
00:28:57,740 --> 00:28:58,599
No, no, no, don't.

756
00:28:58,839 --> 00:28:59,779
Let me call her.

757
00:28:59,799 --> 00:29:00,279
No, no, no.

758
00:29:01,039 --> 00:29:01,859
Don't provoke her.

759
00:29:02,160 --> 00:29:03,380
Listen to me, just ignore her.

760
00:29:05,559 --> 00:29:07,660
You're just too soft.

761
00:29:08,099 --> 00:29:09,599
Always feeling you owe her.

762
00:29:10,259 --> 00:29:11,900
And she's got you wrapped around her finger.

763
00:29:13,180 --> 00:29:13,660
How about this?

764
00:29:14,180 --> 00:29:15,180
In a couple days, I'll call her

765
00:29:15,180 --> 00:29:15,779
and tell her to come back.

766
00:29:16,140 --> 00:29:16,900
Then you can deal with her.

767
00:29:20,039 --> 00:29:21,059
Take my advice.

768
00:29:22,160 --> 00:29:23,359
Even if Old Qian's not doing great,

769
00:29:23,740 --> 00:29:24,519
you've still got money

770
00:29:24,619 --> 00:29:25,720
invested with me, right?

771
00:29:27,220 --> 00:29:27,740
What's there to worry about?

772
00:29:29,299 --> 00:29:30,200
Alright, alright, alright.

773
00:29:31,660 --> 00:29:32,579
Hurry up and eat your noodles.

774
00:29:46,160 --> 00:29:47,200
How much money I've got left,

775
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:50,220
don't I know it myself?

776
00:29:50,819 --> 00:29:52,240
Anyway, with my investments,

777
00:29:52,640 --> 00:29:53,980
only profits, no losses.

778
00:29:54,799 --> 00:29:55,500
You should be secretly thrilled.

779
00:30:03,779 --> 00:30:05,259
That looks like Shu Qingcang.

780
00:30:06,519 --> 00:30:07,119
Shu Qingcang?

781
00:30:08,059 --> 00:30:08,440
Where?

782
00:30:09,980 --> 00:30:10,319
Over there.

783
00:30:12,799 --> 00:30:13,519
Why is he here?

784
00:30:14,980 --> 00:30:15,839
Who knows.

785
00:30:22,900 --> 00:30:24,039
Why is that car back here again?

786
00:30:25,380 --> 00:30:26,900
Stop staring, stop thinking about it.

787
00:30:27,140 --> 00:30:28,759
You're the one who rejected the daughter-in-law.

788
00:30:28,900 --> 00:30:30,200
What's the point of watching her now?

789
00:30:33,519 --> 00:30:34,440
Isn't that Xiaofang?

790
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:35,559
Has she landed some rich guy?

791
00:30:36,039 --> 00:30:37,039
Coming from the city,

792
00:30:37,079 --> 00:30:38,900
maybe he's got some inside info?

793
00:30:39,700 --> 00:30:40,539
What inside info?

794
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:42,980
This Yang Xiaofang

795
00:30:43,079 --> 00:30:43,859
is quite the operator.

796
00:30:44,400 --> 00:30:45,339
On one hand, she's got your son

797
00:30:45,339 --> 00:30:46,039
completely devoted to her.

798
00:30:46,380 --> 00:30:46,799
On the other hand,

799
00:30:48,039 --> 00:30:48,920
she's already in a luxury car.

800
00:30:49,119 --> 00:30:49,940
Morals are going down the drain.

801
00:30:50,380 --> 00:30:51,220
Ethics have collapsed.

802
00:30:52,180 --> 00:30:53,920
The one who ate the poisonous mushrooms is feeling better.

803
00:30:54,279 --> 00:30:55,220
Quick, come take a look!

804
00:30:55,799 --> 00:30:56,539
Come on, right now,

805
00:30:56,819 --> 00:30:58,200
something juicier than poisoned mushrooms.

806
00:31:12,279 --> 00:31:13,140
So rude.

807
00:31:16,119 --> 00:31:16,559
Here, take it.

808
00:31:16,900 --> 00:31:17,920
Thank you, Grand-uncle.

809
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:18,859
May you, Grand-uncle,

810
00:31:18,900 --> 00:31:20,259
have lucky days as swift as the wind,

811
00:31:20,460 --> 00:31:21,759
bountiful years soaring like a kite,

812
00:31:21,900 --> 00:31:23,220
more blessings, more wealth, longer life,

813
00:31:23,400 --> 00:31:24,720
long as mountains, deep as seas, everlasting.

814
00:31:25,539 --> 00:31:26,940
This kid's tongue,

815
00:31:27,240 --> 00:31:28,220
so slick!

816
00:31:28,500 --> 00:31:29,079
Really impressive.

817
00:31:29,319 --> 00:31:30,500
I told you already,

818
00:31:30,519 --> 00:31:32,680
watch fewer short videos.

819
00:31:33,460 --> 00:31:34,720
Well, this kid's smart.

820
00:31:35,220 --> 00:31:36,599
He's got a bright future ahead.

821
00:31:37,160 --> 00:31:37,720
Manxia,

822
00:31:38,039 --> 00:31:38,980
you're truly blessed.

823
00:31:39,359 --> 00:31:40,519
Sons and daughters both,

824
00:31:40,940 --> 00:31:42,140
grandchildren all around,

825
00:31:43,579 --> 00:31:44,700
a flourishing family.

826
00:31:45,220 --> 00:31:46,359
Thanks to your blessing.

827
00:31:47,960 --> 00:31:48,599
Xiaofang,

828
00:31:48,980 --> 00:31:50,839
you need to eat more these days.

829
00:31:51,380 --> 00:31:52,180
Get more nutrition.

830
00:31:52,740 --> 00:31:53,700
It's really important.

831
00:31:54,200 --> 00:31:54,660
Xiao Shu,

832
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:55,660
take care of her.

833
00:31:57,140 --> 00:31:57,619
No problem.

834
00:31:58,220 --> 00:31:58,839
Have a shrimp.

835
00:31:59,660 --> 00:32:00,299
Just peeled it.

836
00:32:00,940 --> 00:32:01,299
This one.

837
00:32:02,420 --> 00:32:03,599
Whole grains, they're good for you.

838
00:32:03,680 --> 00:32:03,980
Here.

839
00:32:05,099 --> 00:32:06,420
Thanks, I can do it myself.

840
00:32:06,799 --> 00:32:08,000
It's fine, I know it's hard for you.

841
00:32:10,099 --> 00:32:10,819
Here comes the main dish!

842
00:32:12,420 --> 00:32:13,039
Braised pork!

843
00:32:13,920 --> 00:32:15,119
Let me say a few words.

844
00:32:17,500 --> 00:32:18,720
Seeing this dish,

845
00:32:19,519 --> 00:32:20,099
I...

846
00:32:20,980 --> 00:32:22,119
have so many feelings.

847
00:32:22,420 --> 00:32:24,200
It reminds me of the old days.

848
00:32:24,740 --> 00:32:26,019
I remember my youngest son,

849
00:32:26,660 --> 00:32:27,740
on his birthday,

850
00:32:28,720 --> 00:32:29,539
he said to me, "Dad,

851
00:32:31,279 --> 00:32:32,599
I want a meal of braised pork."

852
00:32:32,960 --> 00:32:34,059
But back then, I was poor.

853
00:32:34,440 --> 00:32:35,000
Couldn't afford it.

854
00:32:35,400 --> 00:32:36,059
I looked at

855
00:32:36,420 --> 00:32:38,420
my son's pitiful little eyes,

856
00:32:39,380 --> 00:32:40,740
and swore to myself,

857
00:32:41,039 --> 00:32:42,680
if I ever made something of myself,

858
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:44,720
on the Yang family's table,

859
00:32:44,940 --> 00:32:46,059
there'd be meat at every meal.

860
00:32:58,700 --> 00:33:00,240
After hearing Uncle Yang's teachings,

861
00:33:01,019 --> 00:33:03,839
I feel enlightened, like a spring breeze.

862
00:33:04,160 --> 00:33:05,059
It made me realize

863
00:33:05,720 --> 00:33:07,240
the importance of following the right person.

864
00:33:08,640 --> 00:33:09,859
My family used to be poor, too.

865
00:33:11,359 --> 00:33:12,240
My father

866
00:33:12,859 --> 00:33:14,019
gave me life,

867
00:33:14,940 --> 00:33:15,859
but Uncle Yang

868
00:33:17,140 --> 00:33:18,339
gave me a life worth living.

869
00:33:19,799 --> 00:33:21,759
Ever since I followed Uncle Yang,

870
00:33:22,319 --> 00:33:22,920
my family

871
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:24,640
can finally afford to eat meat.

872
00:33:25,160 --> 00:33:27,039
This reminds me of that old saying:

873
00:33:27,460 --> 00:33:28,279
Follow the right person,

874
00:33:28,940 --> 00:33:30,900
and even wrong things become right.

875
00:33:31,799 --> 00:33:32,740
Follow the wrong person,

876
00:33:33,140 --> 00:33:35,460
and even right things become wrong.

877
00:33:37,200 --> 00:33:37,759
Uncle Yang,

878
00:33:38,200 --> 00:33:39,579
you are the right person

879
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:40,819
in my life.

880
00:33:41,619 --> 00:33:42,220
I hope

881
00:33:42,680 --> 00:33:44,559
I can closely follow Uncle Yang's footsteps,

882
00:33:45,500 --> 00:33:45,960
so that I—

883
00:33:46,759 --> 00:33:47,119
No,

884
00:33:48,180 --> 00:33:49,539
so that all our lives

885
00:33:50,160 --> 00:33:51,019
can get better.

886
00:33:51,619 --> 00:33:52,119
Come, come, come.

887
00:33:53,619 --> 00:33:54,259
Tea in place of wine,

888
00:33:54,740 --> 00:33:55,539
let me toast you first.

889
00:33:55,940 --> 00:33:57,000
What kind of nonsense is that?

890
00:33:57,059 --> 00:33:58,279
Learn a thing or two from him.

891
00:33:59,220 --> 00:34:00,180
Words from the heart!

892
00:34:01,720 --> 00:34:02,740
So talented!

893
00:34:03,759 --> 00:34:05,000
It's all thanks to Uncle Yang's guidance.

894
00:34:07,940 --> 00:34:09,219
Xiangyong, Xiangdong,

895
00:34:09,539 --> 00:34:10,340
you both have kids, right?

896
00:34:10,360 --> 00:34:11,119
Yes.

897
00:34:11,340 --> 00:34:12,260
We do, yes,

898
00:34:12,460 --> 00:34:13,639
but not a single one with a handle.

899
00:34:14,800 --> 00:34:15,179
Mom,

900
00:34:15,440 --> 00:34:16,679
what does "one with a handle" mean?

901
00:34:18,480 --> 00:34:19,820
You're one with a handle.

902
00:34:21,320 --> 00:34:22,619
As the old saying goes,

903
00:34:23,420 --> 00:34:24,579
no matter how tall a tree grows,

904
00:34:24,900 --> 00:34:25,960
its leaves return to the roots.

905
00:34:26,420 --> 00:34:27,739
I have only one wish now.

906
00:34:28,639 --> 00:34:29,920
The Yang family bloodline

907
00:34:30,260 --> 00:34:31,300
cannot end

908
00:34:31,320 --> 00:34:32,039
with me.

909
00:34:34,199 --> 00:34:34,760
Fangfang,

910
00:34:36,000 --> 00:34:36,500
eat more,

911
00:34:36,840 --> 00:34:37,840
get more nutrition.

912
00:34:38,679 --> 00:34:39,960
You're our great hero!

913
00:34:41,719 --> 00:34:42,219
In the future,

914
00:34:42,719 --> 00:34:44,360
when our Yang Bite studies in the county,

915
00:34:44,840 --> 00:34:46,139
you can come to me for help.

916
00:34:47,860 --> 00:34:49,059
Grand-uncle, you mean Yang Bite—

917
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:55,039
What I mean is,

918
00:34:55,940 --> 00:34:56,559
what I'm saying is,

919
00:34:58,380 --> 00:34:58,920
Fangfang,

920
00:34:59,400 --> 00:35:00,380
you young people

921
00:35:00,380 --> 00:35:01,639
must take care of each other.

922
00:35:02,659 --> 00:35:03,159
From now on,

923
00:35:03,659 --> 00:35:04,480
if you have any troubles

924
00:35:04,719 --> 00:35:06,000
in life or with money,

925
00:35:06,239 --> 00:35:07,360
just come to Grand-uncle.

926
00:35:08,260 --> 00:35:09,599
We're not strangers, you know.

927
00:35:10,760 --> 00:35:11,360
Thank you, Uncle Yang.

928
00:35:12,639 --> 00:35:13,099
Have some food.

929
00:35:13,380 --> 00:35:13,699
Come on.

930
00:35:15,659 --> 00:35:16,500
Everything I needed to say,

931
00:35:17,440 --> 00:35:18,139
I've said.

932
00:35:18,980 --> 00:35:20,639
I believe they got the message.

933
00:35:21,179 --> 00:35:22,039
You mean

934
00:35:22,139 --> 00:35:23,099
asking for the baby?

935
00:35:25,019 --> 00:35:25,679
I feel like they

936
00:35:25,699 --> 00:35:27,019
didn't quite get it.

937
00:35:27,719 --> 00:35:28,840
Is it really that hard to understand?

938
00:35:29,920 --> 00:35:30,420
It's not your fault.

939
00:35:30,619 --> 00:35:32,179
They're just not sharp enough,

940
00:35:32,179 --> 00:35:32,900
slow on the uptake.

941
00:35:33,380 --> 00:35:34,659
So you need to hammer it in,

942
00:35:35,179 --> 00:35:36,579
make sure they understand.

943
00:35:37,079 --> 00:35:38,219
Got it, got it.

944
00:35:41,239 --> 00:35:41,659
So,

945
00:35:42,159 --> 00:35:44,420
about my internship becoming permanent next year...

946
00:35:44,739 --> 00:35:46,360
Although with the company bosses,

947
00:35:46,380 --> 00:35:47,500
I do have some pull,

948
00:35:47,940 --> 00:35:48,360
but

949
00:35:48,739 --> 00:35:49,679
success depends on effort.

950
00:35:50,659 --> 00:35:52,340
When it counts, you'll have to rely on yourself.

951
00:35:53,480 --> 00:35:54,539
I'll keep your teachings in mind.

952
00:35:55,480 --> 00:35:56,820
You're like a second father to me.

953
00:35:57,280 --> 00:35:57,780
Without you,

954
00:35:57,960 --> 00:35:58,980
I wouldn't be where I am today.

955
00:35:59,679 --> 00:36:00,820
I'm like your own son.

956
00:36:02,119 --> 00:36:03,239
So about the baby thing,

957
00:36:03,239 --> 00:36:04,480
you absolutely have to make it happen.

958
00:36:05,019 --> 00:36:05,480
Understood.

959
00:36:09,199 --> 00:36:10,039
Take care on your way.

960
00:36:15,019 --> 00:36:15,659
Waiter, pack this up.

961
00:37:11,980 --> 00:37:12,820
Is that him?

962
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:13,699
That's him.

963
00:37:14,619 --> 00:37:16,000
What are you worried about?

964
00:37:16,239 --> 00:37:17,760
I already looked into everything for you.

965
00:37:17,960 --> 00:37:19,019
That guy at his workplace

966
00:37:19,219 --> 00:37:20,239
is just an intern.

967
00:37:20,719 --> 00:37:21,860
His pay, compared to regular staff,

968
00:37:22,139 --> 00:37:22,940
is only half as much.

969
00:37:23,420 --> 00:37:24,119
Nothing to brag about.

970
00:37:24,500 --> 00:37:25,400
But doesn't he have

971
00:37:25,679 --> 00:37:26,940
a car too?

972
00:37:27,480 --> 00:37:28,380
What does Xiaowei have?

973
00:37:29,139 --> 00:37:30,420
Why are you boosting his ego?

974
00:37:31,059 --> 00:37:31,420
Relax.

975
00:37:32,119 --> 00:37:33,179
I checked out that car too.

976
00:37:33,800 --> 00:37:34,719
It's not even his.

977
00:37:34,980 --> 00:37:35,579
A conman.

978
00:37:36,260 --> 00:37:36,780
A marriage scammer!

979
00:37:37,559 --> 00:37:39,320
This Shu guy is definitely shady.

980
00:37:39,559 --> 00:37:40,219
He's got ulterior motives.

981
00:37:41,460 --> 00:37:42,579
I won't let my Fang'er

982
00:37:42,719 --> 00:37:44,440
climb out of one mess

983
00:37:44,739 --> 00:37:45,840
just to fall into another.

984
00:37:50,239 --> 00:37:50,840
Did he just

985
00:37:50,840 --> 00:37:51,780
insult himself too?

986
00:37:56,500 --> 00:37:57,039
Where is he?

987
00:37:57,320 --> 00:37:57,900
Just up ahead.

988
00:37:58,119 --> 00:37:58,900
Today we've got to teach

989
00:37:58,900 --> 00:37:59,739
this Shu guy a lesson.

990
00:38:00,980 --> 00:38:01,320
Right here.

991
00:38:07,260 --> 00:38:08,239
Is this really gonna work?

992
00:38:09,800 --> 00:38:11,039
The most sophisticated wars

993
00:38:11,199 --> 00:38:12,920
are often won with the simplest methods.

994
00:38:13,320 --> 00:38:13,800
Let's do this.

995
00:38:28,800 --> 00:38:29,800
Run, run, run, run!

996
00:38:34,860 --> 00:38:35,739
Hey, buddy.

997
00:38:36,239 --> 00:38:38,300
I really don't think you need to do this.

998
00:38:39,380 --> 00:38:40,340
Don't be shy.

999
00:38:40,940 --> 00:38:42,460
Driving the boss around every day,

1000
00:38:42,460 --> 00:38:43,440
your neck and shoulders must be sore.

1001
00:38:43,440 --> 00:38:43,960
Keep pressing.

1002
00:38:44,880 --> 00:38:46,500
I'm saying, you really don't have to.

1003
00:38:46,940 --> 00:38:48,679
Don't let the plain look fool you.

1004
00:38:48,679 --> 00:38:49,639
I've asked around.

1005
00:38:49,679 --> 00:38:51,440
This master's quite famous around here.

1006
00:38:51,500 --> 00:38:52,820
He only opens two hours a day.

1007
00:38:53,039 --> 00:38:54,219
Booking a spot is really tough.

1008
00:38:54,480 --> 00:38:54,980
Boss!

1009
00:38:55,260 --> 00:38:57,099
One bowl of beef sour-soup handmade rice noodles.

1010
00:38:57,099 --> 00:38:57,719
Over there, please.

1011
00:38:58,000 --> 00:38:58,539
What the heck?

1012
00:38:59,179 --> 00:39:00,599
Master, show us your skills!

1013
00:39:03,059 --> 00:39:04,440
Okay, okay, stop, stop!

1014
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:05,239
Really, no need for that.

1015
00:39:06,019 --> 00:39:06,340
Look here.

1016
00:39:06,960 --> 00:39:08,019
Buddy, if you've got something to say,

1017
00:39:08,039 --> 00:39:09,480
just tell me straight up.

1018
00:39:15,280 --> 00:39:16,840
Just get to the point.

1019
00:39:20,500 --> 00:39:22,159
A dragon in shallow water gets mocked by shrimp.

1020
00:39:22,199 --> 00:39:23,519
A tiger on flat ground gets bullied by dogs.

1021
00:39:24,360 --> 00:39:25,880
Brother, I'm just going through

1022
00:39:25,920 --> 00:39:26,679
a bit of a rough patch.

1023
00:39:27,119 --> 00:39:27,500
See?

1024
00:39:28,139 --> 00:39:29,000
I knew you had something going on.

1025
00:39:31,460 --> 00:39:32,739
Life has its ups and downs.

1026
00:39:33,059 --> 00:39:33,719
It's totally normal.

1027
00:39:34,519 --> 00:39:36,019
When it counts, you rely on friends.

1028
00:39:36,199 --> 00:39:36,639
Here's what you do.

1029
00:39:37,079 --> 00:39:38,179
Whatever it is, just say it.

1030
00:39:38,840 --> 00:39:39,420
And I'll

1031
00:39:40,119 --> 00:39:40,780
handle it all in one go.

1032
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:42,300
One-stop service.

1033
00:39:43,719 --> 00:39:44,820
But let me be upfront.

1034
00:39:45,420 --> 00:39:46,579
What I can help with, I'll help.

1035
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:48,079
What I can't help with,

1036
00:39:49,880 --> 00:39:51,019
I'll break my rules to help you.

1037
00:39:53,760 --> 00:39:55,000
With those words from you,

1038
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:57,139
I'm about to start borrowing money.

1039
00:39:58,260 --> 00:39:59,159
Money's no problem.

1040
00:39:59,280 --> 00:39:59,780
How much?

1041
00:40:00,519 --> 00:40:00,940
Fi—

1042
00:40:01,019 --> 00:40:01,480
Five hundred?

1043
00:40:01,699 --> 00:40:02,340
Five hundred, I'll transfer it now.

1044
00:40:02,340 --> 00:40:02,760
Fifty thousand.

1045
00:40:03,059 --> 00:40:03,440
How much?

1046
00:40:03,900 --> 00:40:04,840
Fifty thousand. Recently

1047
00:40:05,099 --> 00:40:06,420
I just joined a financial project,

1048
00:40:06,420 --> 00:40:07,599
and I'm short 50,000 yuan

1049
00:40:07,599 --> 00:40:08,059
in cash flow.

1050
00:40:08,059 --> 00:40:09,280
I'll only need it two days, then pay you back.

1051
00:40:09,480 --> 00:40:10,019
Just two days.

1052
00:40:11,320 --> 00:40:12,699
Cang, Cang, Cang, Cang, Cang!

1053
00:40:13,079 --> 00:40:14,400
You— help me out this once,

1054
00:40:14,820 --> 00:40:15,840
and I'll help you next time you need it.

1055
00:40:19,639 --> 00:40:21,420
You must handle the child's issue for sure.

1056
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:23,340
Yes, yes, understood.

1057
00:40:27,239 --> 00:40:28,059
Did I say I was leaving?

1058
00:40:30,340 --> 00:40:32,300
I'm just a little jealous of you.

1059
00:40:33,480 --> 00:40:34,219
So young,

1060
00:40:34,219 --> 00:40:35,480
and already into finance projects.

1061
00:40:37,519 --> 00:40:38,780
How does that saying go again?

1062
00:40:39,139 --> 00:40:42,760
Gone half a lifetime, still a youth on return.

1063
00:40:43,360 --> 00:40:43,719
Master.

1064
00:40:44,079 --> 00:40:45,659
I admire your courage.

1065
00:40:46,360 --> 00:40:47,039
And not just you.

1066
00:40:47,880 --> 00:40:49,099
Even your niece, Xiaofang,

1067
00:40:50,440 --> 00:40:51,800
she really dares to think and act.

1068
00:40:52,639 --> 00:40:54,260
With that Xiaowei guy,

1069
00:40:55,159 --> 00:40:56,260
she cut him off just like that.

1070
00:40:58,159 --> 00:40:59,059
It's over.

1071
00:40:59,579 --> 00:41:00,659
Us Yangs,

1072
00:41:01,360 --> 00:41:02,139
we lack a lot of things,

1073
00:41:02,599 --> 00:41:03,860
but we've never lacked backbone.

1074
00:41:04,179 --> 00:41:05,119
现在啊
Translation>
Now,

1075
00:41:05,119 --> 00:41:06,440
even if Xiaowei begged on his knees,

1076
00:41:06,440 --> 00:41:07,780
Xiaofang wouldn't give him the time of day.

1077
00:41:08,880 --> 00:41:09,400
Really?

1078
00:41:12,500 --> 00:41:12,940
Impressive.

1079
00:41:13,699 --> 00:41:14,920
That said,

1080
00:41:15,460 --> 00:41:16,679
Xiaofang's so young.

1081
00:41:16,679 --> 00:41:18,000
She'll definitely find someone else later.

1082
00:41:18,619 --> 00:41:20,460
But bringing a kid along is such a hassle.

1083
00:41:20,940 --> 00:41:22,400
Ever thought of giving the child away?

1084
00:41:22,920 --> 00:41:23,619
No way.

1085
00:41:23,960 --> 00:41:24,719
Absolutely not.

1086
00:41:25,460 --> 00:41:26,360
With the Yang family backbone,

1087
00:41:26,360 --> 00:41:27,340
we don't do such shameless things.

1088
00:41:28,219 --> 00:41:28,579
No way.

1089
00:41:33,420 --> 00:41:34,460
That makes things tough.

1090
00:41:34,940 --> 00:41:36,440
What's so tough about it?

1091
00:41:37,199 --> 00:41:38,780
People lining up to meet Xiaofang

1092
00:41:38,780 --> 00:41:39,840
are in a long queue.

1093
00:41:40,159 --> 00:41:41,559
Can't even meet them all in a day.

1094
00:41:41,559 --> 00:41:42,159
Not tough at all.

1095
00:41:43,139 --> 00:41:44,460
When she meets the right one,

1096
00:41:44,820 --> 00:41:46,039
won't the kid have a dad?

1097
00:41:51,440 --> 00:41:52,219
Fate.

1098
00:41:53,500 --> 00:41:53,920
Yes.

1099
00:41:56,980 --> 00:41:58,559
Fate.

1100
00:42:04,059 --> 00:42:05,460
And fate,

1101
00:42:05,940 --> 00:42:07,559
isn't that ruled by the God of Wealth too?

1102
00:42:14,659 --> 00:42:15,099
Lao Cang

1103
00:42:16,099 --> 00:42:16,659
Lao Cang

1104
00:42:16,659 --> 00:42:17,860
I knew you could help me

1105
00:42:18,300 --> 00:42:19,199
Thank you, Lao Cang

1106
00:42:20,239 --> 00:42:20,820
Zhu'er

1107
00:42:22,179 --> 00:42:23,420
You know, a guy like me

1108
00:42:24,260 --> 00:42:25,840
might seem a bit worldly

1109
00:42:26,219 --> 00:42:27,739
but deep down inside

1110
00:42:28,159 --> 00:42:29,780
I'm just like you

1111
00:42:30,500 --> 00:42:31,340
just like Xiaofang

1112
00:42:34,880 --> 00:42:36,179
I long for true love too

1113
00:42:38,320 --> 00:42:39,099
Lao Cang, this...

1114
00:42:39,980 --> 00:42:40,599
this isn't appropriate

1115
00:42:41,480 --> 00:42:42,139
this isn't appropriate

1116
00:42:42,300 --> 00:42:43,280
What's inappropriate about it?

1117
00:42:43,280 --> 00:42:43,639
It's just not right

1118
00:42:43,639 --> 00:42:44,480
I really think that

1119
00:42:44,880 --> 00:42:46,840
your Xiaofang is a wonderful girl

1120
00:42:48,119 --> 00:42:49,119
What?

1121
00:42:50,440 --> 00:42:51,579
I treat you like a brother

1122
00:42:52,380 --> 00:42:53,960
and you want to be my niece's husband?

1123
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:55,320
What?

1124
00:42:55,960 --> 00:42:57,039
He's got his eye on Xiaofang

1125
00:42:57,300 --> 00:42:58,360
It sounds absurd

1126
00:42:58,480 --> 00:42:59,579
but it's the absolute truth

1127
00:43:00,420 --> 00:43:01,719
See, what did I tell you

1128
00:43:02,599 --> 00:43:03,760
When Uncle wanted to play matchmaker that day

1129
00:43:04,059 --> 00:43:05,059
none of you believed it

1130
00:43:05,619 --> 00:43:06,559
Now you get it, right?

1131
00:43:07,380 --> 00:43:08,420
But I think

1132
00:43:08,920 --> 00:43:10,159
this Xiao Cang isn't much of a catch

1133
00:43:10,860 --> 00:43:12,500
If he got a permanent position, maybe then

1134
00:43:13,139 --> 00:43:13,900
Fanzhu, I think

1135
00:43:16,260 --> 00:43:16,760
Make a call

1136
00:43:18,280 --> 00:43:19,360
Set up a meeting with Xiao Cang for me

1137
00:43:23,639 --> 00:43:25,639
I'm the biological father of Yang Xiaofang's child

1138
00:43:25,860 --> 00:43:26,480
I'm warning you

1139
00:43:26,659 --> 00:43:27,480
Stay away from her

1140
00:43:28,099 --> 00:43:29,699
A second marriage is worse than a dog's life

1141
00:43:29,840 --> 00:43:30,980
Xiaofang's best bet

1142
